   MAGAZINES: Reader's Digest Association Inc. will launch
Budgets Famille next October through its French subsidiary.
The monthly magazine, designed to help families manage their
finances, is the company's first magazine start-up in France
since it began publishing a French-language edition of
Reader's Digest in 1947.
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   WHO'S NEWS: Nancy Klopper was named senior vice president,
production, for Act III Communications Inc.'s Act III
Productions division. She was vice president, talent and
artist relations, at Twentieth Century Fox. . . . MGM/UA
Communications Co. named Leanna J. Heath to the new post of
vice president, senior production counsel. She had been a
partner with Bushkin, Gaims, Gaines &amp; Jones.
